## Working Principle

The Smart Car Parking System works by combining sensors, microcontrollers, and a web interface to automate parking management.

1. IR sensors are placed at parking slots and entry points to detect the presence of vehicles.

2. The sensor data is processed by the ESP32 and Arduino microcontrollers.

3. The ESP32 hosts a web server through Wi-Fi, which displays the real-time status of parking slots as Empty or Occupied.

4. When a vehicle arrives at the entrance, the IR sensor detects it and the LCD prompts the user to scan the QR code.

5. After entry, the Arduino controls the servo motor to automatically open and close the gate barrier.

6. As vehicles occupy or leave parking slots, the sensor readings update the website dynamically.

7. The system provides real-time parking monitoring and demonstrates the integration of embedded systems, IoT, automation, and web technologies.
